ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_sp | |- ( A. x x = y -> x = y ) |
| 2 | 1 | #P_con3i | |- ( -. x = y -> -. A. x x = y ) |
| 3 |  | #P_sp | |- ( A. x x = z -> x = z ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_con3i | |- ( -. x = z -> -. A. x x = z ) |
| 5 |  | #P_axc9 | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( -. A. x x = z -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) ) |
| 6 | 2, 4, 5 | #P_syl2im | |- ( -. x = y -> ( -. x = z -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) ) |
| 7 |  | #P_ax13b | |- ( ( -. x = y -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) <-> ( -. x = y -> ( -. x = z -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) ) ) |
| 8 | 6, 7 | #P_mpbir | |- ( -. x = y -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) |
\
 Derive ~ ax-13 from ~ ax13v via ~ axc9 .  This shows that the weakening in ~ ax13v is still sufficient for a complete system.  (Contributed by NM, 21-Dec-2015.)  (Proof shortened by Wolf Lammen, 31-Jan-2018.)
